His spine is a little crooked.

12
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:36,140
When he carried me down
the stairs yesterday,

13
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:37,570
I felt it.

14
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:39,650
To be frank,

15
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,880
after I turned 14,

16
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:44,250
I haven't seen much of him.

17
00:02:46,390 --> 00:02:48,210
It's highly unlikely that I had caused

18
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,720
his back to be crooked.

19
00:02:52,470 --> 00:02:54,130
In my memory,

20
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:56,650
I remember how he would carry me

21
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:58,830
me on his shoulders when I was a kid

22
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,940
and held me high up.

23
00:03:04,550 --> 00:03:05,610
Now,

24
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,240
how did his spine become crooked?

25
00:03:11,410 --> 00:03:13,060
Perhaps it's lack of calcium.

26
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,680
I know about those scientific

27
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:20,810
What I wish to say is,

28
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,729
just because this man

29
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:25,770
wears a police uniform,

30
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:28,500
I had believed that

31
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:30,290
he was invincible.

32
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:35,290
Who knew he'd get exhausted too?

33
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,370
Maybe other people don't see it.

34
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,080
He himself doesn't see it.

35
00:03:40,850 --> 00:03:42,550
But I can.

36
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,160
His back is crooked.

37
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,600
I'm heartbroken.

38
00:04:00,420 --> 00:04:02,030
Just like you said,

39
00:04:03,930 --> 00:04:05,710
I still hate him.

40
00:04:06,690 --> 00:04:09,070
Still, I wish I could do
something for him.

41
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,050
But I'm just a lunatic.

42
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:15,800
You're not.

43
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:20,770
You know what I said to him yesterday?

44
00:04:21,429 --> 00:04:22,419
I said,

45
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:24,160
"Stay away from me."

46
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:26,489
"I hate you."

47
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:40,290
If he doesn't wake up,

48
00:04:42,059 --> 00:04:44,370
that would be the last thing

49
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:46,720
I ever said to him.

50
00:04:49,510 --> 00:04:50,880
That would be

51
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:54,480
our farewell.

52
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,290
Perhaps this is a hint from God.

53
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,490
Only that

54
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:15,570
it was done in a more dangerous way.

55
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:19,210
Right.

56
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:21,430
A huge hint this is.

57
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,270
<i>Blood connection</i>

58
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,940
<i>is stronger than you think.</i>

59
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,680
<i>Xiao Xue.</i>

60
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:33,420
<i>Just because he doesn't
convey his emotions</i>

61
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:34,650
<i>wilfully like you</i>

62
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:36,410
<i>doesn't mean he doesn't care.</i>

63
00:05:42,340 --> 00:05:44,690
Daddy, I feel sick.

64
00:05:44,850 --> 00:05:46,510
I want to go home.

65
00:05:47,309 --> 00:05:48,820
I'll take you home
once you finish the drip.

66
00:05:48,910 --> 00:05:49,660
Be good.

67
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,860
Please.

68
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:52,660
I want to go home now.

69
00:05:52,790 --> 00:05:54,090
Be good, Tian Tian.

70
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:56,530
I'll buy you delicious snacks
when you finish the drip,

71
00:05:56,630 --> 00:05:57,650
okay?

72
00:05:58,050 --> 00:06:00,030
You mean it, right?

73
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:02,010
Promise me you'll stay with me too.

74
00:06:02,110 --> 00:06:03,340
You mustn't leave.

75
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:04,620
I promise you,

76
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:06,460
I'll stay by your side.

77
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:07,260
Okay.

78
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:08,650
Pinky promise.

79
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:12,010
Pinky promise binds you

80
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,860
to the word for 100 years.

81
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:15,770
If you break it, you'll become a dog.

82
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,490
Good girl.

83
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:24,470
Do you have pen and paper?

84
00:06:25,030 --> 00:06:26,010
I'll get some.

85
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,420
What's this?

86
00:07:51,559 --> 00:07:53,520
I modified it using
the unit's bulletproof vest.

87
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:55,950
I use it when I'm dressed
in civilian clothing.

88
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,730
I want you to have it.

89
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,420
What for?

90
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,280
To keep you safe.

91
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:04,340
I'm wearing a bra.

92
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,850
How am I supposed to wear this?

93
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:13,780
Maybe go back and try to...

94
00:08:14,930 --> 00:08:16,790
Try to find a way.

95
00:08:18,150 --> 00:08:19,460
Such a straight guy.

96
00:08:19,550 --> 00:08:21,540
Put away the heart protector.

97
00:08:21,620 --> 00:08:23,290
I don't want to catch sight of it.

98
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:24,770
Why?

99
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:26,190
It's ugly.

100
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,730
Isn't is obvious?

101
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:29,500
I don't want to see it.

102
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,610
Is it ugly?

103
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,420
You still donated blood
despite your injury?

104
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,250
Worry about yourself first, Dr Xia.

105
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,610
I'm doing good.

106
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:56,570
Good?

107
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:58,390
That parcel was sent to you.

108
00:08:58,470 --> 00:08:59,660
If you got blown up by it,

109
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:00,890
would you still be good?

110
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:04,510
Were you worried about me?

111
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,820
Of course.

112
00:09:11,790 --> 00:09:13,260
Who was the sender?

113
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,690
The police is still investigating.

114
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:32,950
My coffee.

115
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:33,830
Don't move.

116
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:34,930
Come here.

117
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:36,990
What are you doing?

118
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,170
What are you doing? Hey.

119
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:40,250
Sit down.

120
00:09:44,530 --> 00:09:45,380
Relax.

121
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,340
Relax.

122
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,140
Relax.

123
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,000
Enjoy this moment.

124
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:09,730
How is it?

125
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:11,960
Left. The left side.

126
00:10:13,690 --> 00:10:15,190
Yes, that's the spot.

127
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,360
Liang Mu Ze.

128
00:10:26,950 --> 00:10:28,490
With your skills,

129
00:10:28,590 --> 00:10:30,710
you'll be able to run a massage shop.

130
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:32,650
I'm sure you'll have returning customers.

131
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:36,370
This is my family's ancestral skill.

132
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:38,680
However,

133
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:40,500
this skill of ours

134
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:42,420
is reserved

135
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,130
for only one person this whole life.

136
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:53,060
Xia Chu.

137
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:55,690
Do think it over again.

138
00:10:56,190 --> 00:10:57,530
Come to the unit.

139
00:10:59,150 --> 00:11:00,130
Where?

140
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:07,800
♫ Every minute, every second,
how do I resist? ♫

141
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:15,050
♫ I can't help but look forward
to your return ♫

142
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:21,790
♫ To relive the moment
my heart skipped a beat ♫

143
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:16,930
See?

144
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:19,410
We don't have answers to many questions.

145
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,770
But there's one answer

146
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:25,050
that I'm sure of.

147
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,380
What is it?

148
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:33,730
The moon tonight

149
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:35,280
is lovely.

150
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:46,060
Yes, it is.

151
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,340
Alright, Captain Liang.

152
00:11:48,430 --> 00:11:49,020
Thank you.

153
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:50,610
I feel rejuvenated now.

154
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,290
I can return to my work.

155
00:11:53,290 --> 00:11:55,190
Hope your hand recovers well.

156
00:11:57,650 --> 00:11:59,190
Do you still remember the tips

157
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:01,880
I taught you about staying safe?

158
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:06,020
Don't travel alone.

159
00:12:06,110 --> 00:12:07,210
Do not stay in the hotel alone.

160
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:08,220
Set the speed dial

161
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:09,500
to call the police.

162
00:12:09,590 --> 00:12:11,480
Shut the doors and windows
when alone at home.

163
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:13,220
Do not put down the home address
for deliveries.

164
00:12:13,310 --> 00:12:14,500
Take note of the location

165
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:15,690
of lifts, stairs and alarms.

166
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:16,700
Aside from that,

167
00:12:16,790 --> 00:12:18,170
no matter how fast a lift goes,

168
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:19,020
a person running

169
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:20,220
can catch up to it

170
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:21,340
within three floors.

171
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:22,540
So during emergencies,

172
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:23,780
in order to ditch pursuers,

173
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:25,910
choose to go further than three floors.

174
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:26,940
Press more floors if needed

175
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,430
to confuse the pursuer.

176
00:12:28,530 --> 00:12:29,380
Anything around me

177
00:12:29,470 --> 00:12:30,940
can be used as a makeshift weapon.

178
00:12:31,030 --> 00:12:32,380
If I really can't get away,

179
00:12:32,470 --> 00:12:35,360
then go to somewhere with people
and call for help.

180
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,160
Captain Liang.

181
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:38,900
What you've told me,

182
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:41,080
I have them etched in my mind.

183
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,700
I won't forget it.

184
00:12:44,210 --> 00:12:45,310
Not bad.

185
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:47,850
I'm off.

186
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:03,670
Dr Zhang.

187
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:04,690
Doctor.

188
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:05,810
Why are you here?

189
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,470
This is Ke Wei's grandmother.

190
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,790
We just came from the
Public Security Bureau.

191
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:10,240
We were told Ke Wei was sent here.

192
00:13:10,330 --> 00:13:11,590
How is he?

193
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:12,850
Doctor.

194
00:13:13,350 --> 00:13:14,570
He's badly injured.

195
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:17,110
What's most life-threatening is that

196
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,910
the foreign object pierced
through the right atrium

197
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,190
penetrating the heart

198
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,510
and right chest,

199
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,970
straight up the right side of the neck.

200
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:25,440
In addition,

201
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:26,900
the cut in the right atrium

202
00:13:26,990 --> 00:13:28,760
is very close to the coronary artery.

203
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:30,490
We haven't been able to determine

204
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:31,680
if the aorta is damaged.

205
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:32,860
We can only

206
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,740
find out during the operation.

207
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:37,410
Doctor, please, I'm begging you.

208
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,980
You have to save him.

209
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:41,260
He is

210
00:13:41,350 --> 00:13:43,650
the only heir of the family.

211
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:44,920
Madam.

212
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:46,370
Please calm down.

213
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:47,450
Tell me.

214
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:49,100
Does he have any criminal record

215
00:13:49,180 --> 00:13:50,800
or history of mental illness?

216
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:52,490
No, none.

217
00:13:52,570 --> 00:13:54,880
My grandson has always been good.

218
00:13:54,990 --> 00:13:56,490
He's a good kid.

219
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:57,720
Doctor,

220
00:13:57,810 --> 00:14:00,210
this man is very important
in our following investigation.

221
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,900
Please do your best to save him.

222
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:03,900
Don't worry.

223
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:04,460
As a doctor,

224
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,620
we'll do everything in our power.

225
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:06,300
Thank you.

226
00:14:06,390 --> 00:14:08,210
If there are no problems,

227
00:14:08,470 --> 00:14:09,970
please sign this consent form.

228
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:22,130
I can't believe you agreed
to do the operation.

229
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:23,560
What to do.

230
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:24,760
Director Chen is overseas.

231
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:26,130
Dr Lu is sick.

232
00:14:26,410 --> 00:14:28,660
I'm the only one with experience
treating foreign matter penetration.

233
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:29,930
Who else is going to do it?

234
00:14:30,010 --> 00:14:31,560
He blew up several people today.

235
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:33,090
That's why we need to save him,

236
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:34,690
so that he can be interrogated.

237
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,350
Putting aside his injuries,

238
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:38,300
the incident today is a huge deal.

239
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:40,460
Have you considered the risks
of saving him?

240
00:14:40,550 --> 00:14:41,890
The police will be monitoring.

241
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:44,290
Our media department will be
recording the whole process.

242
00:14:45,350 --> 00:14:46,230
Besides,

243
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,130
if something did happen,

244
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:48,390
I could only blame it on bad luck.

245
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:49,730
You can just ignore it.

246
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,490
You should at least wait
for the results

247
00:14:51,570 --> 00:14:52,680
to his infectious diseases check

248
00:14:52,770 --> 00:14:54,110
before performing the operation.

249
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:55,580
There's no time.

250
00:14:55,710 --> 00:14:57,570
He may die at any moment.

251
00:14:57,950 --> 00:14:59,810
Don't worry. I'll be careful.

252
00:15:01,610 --> 00:15:02,580
You're unbelievable.

253
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:04,060
You always think you're right.

254
00:15:04,150 --> 00:15:04,980
Be it at work

255
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,370
or in relationships.

256
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:07,940
You and Chen Meng Zhen

257
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:09,480
are not compatible at all.

258
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:12,770
You and I are compatible.

259
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,650
We're both smart and cautious.

260
00:15:14,740 --> 00:15:15,840
How did that end up?

261
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:17,570
Dr Zhang,

262
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:19,120
the patient's blood pressure is falling.

263
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:26,980
What's the situation?

264
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:28,290
He's spazzing non-stop.

265
00:15:29,310 --> 00:15:30,140
Begin anaesthesia.

266
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:31,110
Okay.

267
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:32,140
Ke Wei,

268
00:15:32,230 --> 00:15:34,090
it doesn't matter what happened before.

269
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:36,020
Right now, you're my patient.

270
00:15:36,110 --> 00:15:37,710
I'm trying to save you.

271
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:39,030
I hope to get your cooperation.

272
00:15:39,110 --> 00:15:40,380
At least, let your family

273
00:15:40,470 --> 00:15:41,810
see you again, all right?

274
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:43,870
Ready to open the chest.

275
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,650
<i>Steady.</i>

276
00:15:58,110 --> 00:15:59,220
<i>Let's finish it in one go.</i>

277
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:00,390
<i>Ready.</i>

278
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,940
<i>One, two.</i>

279
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:05,960
Apply pressure.

280
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:07,170
Use the hemostatic forceps.

281
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,440
Over here.

282
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:12,810
<i>Sorry, sir.</i>

283
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:13,470
It's okay.

284
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:14,690
Stop the bleeding with gauze.

285
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:19,350
I'm going to change my gloves.

286
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,320
Okay.

