335
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:02,630
I won't.

336
00:19:05,710 --> 00:19:06,630
You're so sure?

337
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:10,850
Do you know

338
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:12,980
what the words I heard the most

339
00:19:13,070 --> 00:19:14,170
since young are?

340
00:19:15,560 --> 00:19:16,860
In primary school,

341
00:19:17,410 --> 00:19:18,510
I got first place.

342
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:20,680
The elders and teachers would say,

343
00:19:20,870 --> 00:19:21,900
"A girl"

344
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:23,440
"only performs well in primary school."

345
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:25,680
When I was in middle school,
I got first again.

346
00:19:25,980 --> 00:19:27,680
Once again, the elders and teachers said,

347
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:29,590
"The boys haven't shown
their true power."

348
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:32,720
I got into the Science Experimental Class
in high school.

349
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,940
The Math teacher's favourite phrase was,

350
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:37,590
"I don't expect anything much
from girls on this question."

351
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:39,030
"But if the boys got this wrong,"

352
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,470
"they will be caned."

353
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:42,560
It didn't matter I could answer all of it.

354
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:45,090
When I got into
the Military Medical University,

355
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:46,840
at the start of my internship,

356
00:19:46,950 --> 00:19:48,410
my supervisor would say,

357
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:50,470
"Females are strong in theory."

358
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:51,640
"But when it comes to actual practice,"

359
00:19:51,730 --> 00:19:53,110
"men are still better."

360
00:19:53,870 --> 00:19:55,890
In today's medical environment,

361
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:58,090
